####### CONDA #######
## is a package and an enviroment manager [provided by anaconda or miniconda]
## can manage an entire python environment (both R and python)
## Strengths:
       # Installs compiled binaries (no need to compile from source).
       # Handles nonâ€‘Python dependencies (e.g., R, gcc, BLAS, libpng).
       # Creates isolated environments (conda create -n myenv)

## basic functions in CONDA, to be expleted in powershell
  # conda "create -n" + "python=version" # to create a new environment within python
  # conda "activate" # to activate the environment you created with the last command
  # conda "install -c channel" followed by packages # to install a package
      ### use defaults for basic packages, conda-forge for new or rare packages, bioconda for bioinformatic packages
  # keep in mind that channels arerepository (sources) where conda looks for packages


###### PIP ########
## is a python package manager, also defined as python native installer 
 ## main command
  # pip "install" + package # to install a package
 ## specific installation processes
  # pip "install --upgrade" packages #to update a package
  # pip "install git+https://github.com/..." # to install a package directly from github


